def: Of, pertaining to, or resembling, the Honeysuckle family ofplants (Caprifoliacæ.
The trade or business of selling books.
Having eight sides and eight angles.
To make to understand; to instruct. [Prov. Eng.] Halliwell.
To come to one point; to meet in, or converge toward, a commoncenter; to have a common center.God, in whom all perfections concenter. Bp. Beveridge.
In a discerning manner; with judgment; judiciously; acutely.Garth.
Not reconcilable; implacable; incompatible; inconsistent;disagreeing; as, irreconcilable enemies, statements.-- Ir*rec"on*ci`la*ble*ness, n.-- Ir*rec"on*ci`la*bly, adv.

Of, like, or pertaining to, a deer of the genus Rusa, whichincludes the sambur deer (Rusa Aristotelis) of India. Rusine antler(Zoöl.), an antler with the brow tyne simple, and the beam forked atthe tip.
